    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>To use Zend_Db_Profiler_Firebug when not using the MVC part of Zend Framework requires using Zend_Controller_Response_Http, as shown in the docs:
<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.db.profiler.html#zend.db.profiler.profilers.firebug.example.without_front_controller">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>The problem is Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract always outputs a status code header, which overwrites whatever status code I previously set in my application with 200 OK.</p>

<p>Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract::sendHeaders() checks whether $this-&gt;_httpResponseCode is set, so in theory all I need to do is clear it... But Zend_Controller_Response_Abstract::setHttpResponseCode() throws an exception if I try to set it to null/false/0.</p>

